
[1]cyclopedia

   CYCLOPEDIA, CYCOPEDE, n. [Gr., circle, discipline, erudition.] The
   circle or compass of the arts and sciences; circle of human knowledge.
   Hence, the book or books that contain treatises on every branch of the
   arts and sciences, arranged under proper heads, in alphabetical order.
   [See Encyclopedia.]
